Ligue 1 side, Nice reportedly closing up Lyon striker Amine Gouiri for a fee of €6million (£5.5million) following Celtic’s change of heart. Gouiri is set to leave Lyonand make a switch to Nice in a bid to gain more game time that he is not guaranteed at his current club, According to L’Equipe. Nice are reportedly bringing him to the club to give some healthy competition to Kasper Dolberg in attack, and they consider the youngster to fit the bill. The 20-year-old has managed to make five first-team appearances this season while scoring three goals in from four UEFA Youth League appearances.